name: william
culturalSignificance: The name William has been borne by many kings and leaders throughout history, including William the Conqueror, the first Norman King of England. It has been a popular name in English-speaking countries for centuries, symbolizing strength and leadership.
modernContext: William remains a popular name in many countries, consistently ranking in the top 20 names for boys in the United States and the United Kingdom. Its timeless appeal is attributed to its historical significance and classic sound.
literaryReferences: William Shakespeare, one of the most famous playwrights in history, is a notable literary figure with this name.
personality: People named William are often perceived as strong, reliable, and protective. They are seen as natural leaders with a sense of duty and responsibility.
symbolism: The name William symbolizes protection and determination, often associated with leadership and courage.
funFact: William is one of the most common names among British monarchs, with four kings named William ruling over England.
